benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Add tags to account

covered: Valid Payloads: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05) cover successful tag creation with single/multiple tags and varying headers.

Validation & Error Handling: Scenarios for empty body (TC07), malformed body (TC08), invalid tag definition IDs (TC09), non-existent tag definitions (TC10), missing required header (TC11), missing accountId (TC12), invalid accountId format (TC13), and non-existent account (TC14) cover input validation and resource existence checks.
Authorization & Security: Unauthorized access (TC15) and injection attempt in header (TC22) covered.
Server & Reliability: Service unavailable (TC16) and regression/edge cases (TC23, TC24).
Edge/variant cases: Duplicate tag definitions (TC19), duplicate handling in request body, large payloads (TC18), performance/slow response (TC20), concurrency (TC21).
gaps: Pagination: No concrete test verifying proper pagination handling for large datasets in responses (despite TC06 noting parameters are ignored).
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers or ETag behavior for the response.
Rate Limiting: No tests for handling multiple requests in a short time period.
Authorization depth: Limited coverage beyond missing token (e.g., 403 for insufficient permissions).
recommendations: Add explicit tests for correct pagination behavior with large result sets (beyond ignoring limit/offset).
Add tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on POST responses where applicable.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling scenarios to ensure proper handling under load, and test for 429 where applicable.
Expand authorization tests to cover insufficient-permission scenarios (e.g., 403) in addition to 401 for missing/invalid tokens.
